article.title: Investigation on the reported superconductivity in intercalated black phosphorus

multiple_choice_question.text: What element, besides phosphorus, is consistently present in the EDS analysis of BP-1 and BP-2 crystals but absent in BP-3?
Figure 4a and 4b compare the superconducting transition of intercalated black phosphorus with another material. What is this material?
What type of measurement does Figure 5 represent?
What is the reported superconducting transition temperature (Tc) observed in both the Sn-contaminated intercalated black phosphorus and pure Sn?
